                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment73568965_42733235&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2017-04-06 08:40:16Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Apr 6, 2017 at 8:40&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;process(line)&lt;/code&gt; is a function that you need to implement to process the data. for example, instead of that line, if you use &lt;code&gt;print(line)&lt;/code&gt;, it will print each line from the lines_buffer.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/1306799/khanal&quot; title=&quot;758 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Khanal&lt;/a&gt;
